## 6 Conclusion

Inelastic collisions, only conservation of momentum can be applied.

Conservation of kinetic energy cannot be applied since some of the kinetic energy is transformed into internal energy and sound or other forms of energy.

Similarly, the relationship of Relative speed of approach = Relative speed of separation cannot be applied.

For perfectly inelastic collisions, the two bodies will stick together (sometimes the word coalesce is used) as one single body after collision, i.e. they move off together with a common velocity.

